Port Elizabeth  police detectives are urgently appealing to the community to help  trace the next of kin of a woman whose body was found floating in the sea on Sunday morning. Police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said  a man  fishing   near Sidon Road had spotted the body  at about 8.30am and alerted the National Sea Rescue Institute, who in turn contacted the police. Naidu said the coloured woman, believed to be between 30 and 45 years old, had been wearing only a green top and a black long-sleeve vest when she was retrieved from the water. . Anyone who can assist police in identifying the woman is asked to contact the  Mount Road police onÂ  041-394-6243/39- 6316 or Crime Stop on 08600-10111 or the nearest police station.